# 1. 嬉しい知らせ

Mizuki: I'll throw in that effect here at the end and...
Mizuki: Yes, all done! How awesome is this lace transition?! Not only is it really cute, it goes great with Mafuyu's lyrics too...!
Mizuki: I'll have the others take a look at it now♪ <The music video's all done! I think it turned out really well, so tell me your thoughts!>
Mizuki: Unfortunately, I can't start working on our next song until Ena's finished with her sketch. I guess I just have to wait and see what everyone says...
Mizuki: Wait, now's my chance to do some research!
Mizuki: Let's see... Aha, here's the stuff on lucky bags from the New Year's sales! I gotta start choosing which to get since New Year's is just around the corner.
Mizuki: Wait, this company's also selling some...?! And you can get 30,000 yen's worth of items for just 10,000?! Talk about a bargain!
Mizuki: Where are they selling these...? Oh, the shop at the mall's gonna have some.
Mizuki: I can order it online... But I wanna get one in person and be a part of the festivities♪
Mizuki's Mother's Voice: Mizuki, I just peeled an orange. Would you like a couple slices?
Mizuki: Oh, really?! Yeah, I'd love some!
Mizuki: Thanks, Mom!
Mizuki's Mother: Of course. Oh, also...
Mizuki's Mother: Your sister just called. She said she'll be coming home for New Year's!
Mizuki: Wait, she is...?!
Mizuki's Mother: Yes, her plane's supposed to depart from France on New Year's Eve. She's scheduled to arrive in the evening our time on New Year's Day.
Mizuki: ...! So, she's coming next week?!
Mizuki's Mother: Hehe. Are you excited?
Mizuki: Very...!
Mizuki's Mother: Anyway, I'll leave the orange slices on the table in the living room. Please have some whenever.
Mizuki: Okay, I'll go in a little bit!
Mizuki: Wow, she's really coming home...
Mizuki: We've been calling and sending emails to each other, but it's been so long since we spoke in person... I think I was still in junior high.
Mizuki: There's so much I wanna tell her...
Mizuki: Oh, it's been so long, it'd be great if we could go someplace together. But where...?
Mizuki: I know! The New Year's sales...!
Mizuki: I really wanna go shopping with her, and I bet she's gonna want to see what the fashion scene in Japan's like right now.
Mizuki: (We stopped going as much once I entered junior high, but... We used to go clothes shopping together all the time.)
Mizuki: (I remember wearing some of the clothes that she made herself too.)
Elementary School Mizuki: Wow...!
Mizuki's Sister: Okay, one complete outfit made to order!
Elementary School Mizuki: This is so cool! These shoes and this ribbon are so adorable, and they even go perfectly with the blouse you made for me...!
Elementary School Mizuki: Still, is it really okay for me to dress this cute?
Mizuki's Sister: Of course it is! This outfit looks amazing on you, Mizuki!
Mizuki's Sister: Oh, we should go look at some of those accessories too!
Elementary School Mizuki: Okay...!
Mizuki: We had so much fun back then... And I always loved it when she designed new outfits for me.
Mizuki: Hehe. I really want to return the favor by picking out some cute clothes for her.
Mizuki: Alright, I'll send an email right now to invite her to the big sales...!
Mizuki: <So, because my big sis is coming home for New Year's, I probably won't be able to get much work done.>
Kanade: <That's okay. You should spend as much time with her as you can since it's been so long.>
Ena: <Your big sister works as a fashion designer overseas, right, Amia?>
Mizuki: <That's right! On top of being an amazing designer, she's got an awesome talent for putting outfits together!>
Mizuki: <I plan on checking out the New Year's sales and looking for some cute clothes with her when she gets back♪>
Ena: <Oh, the New Year's sales... I saw that some places are already taking orders for lucky bags. I should check to see what's up on offer.>
Kanade: <Oh, you can order lucky bags online...?>
Ena: <Yeah. Convenient, right? Everywhere is super packed during New Year's, so I'd rather not go outside.>
Mizuki: <Doesn't that mean you're gonna spend most of your holidays sleeping? I know you wanna have a relaxing New Year's, but guess what's gonna happen if all you do is eat and sleep?>
Ena: <Shut up. Between my art class assignments and going around to greet my relatives, I'm going to be pretty busy this year.>
Mafuyu: <Oh...>
Kanade: <Is something wrong, Yuki...?>
Mafuyu: <Nothing's wrong, but... I always spent New Year's with my parents and went around to greet my relatives...>
Ena: <Oh...>
Mizuki: (Yeah, that's a tough one... Normally, New Year's involves spending time with your family...)
Mizuki: <Then, why not go out somewhere to get a breath of fresh air? After all, staying cooped up inside isn't exactly good for your health...!>
Kanade: <For our health... Yes, it's been hard to get myself to go outside since it's been so cold, but a walk might not be a bad idea.>
Mafuyu: <K, didn't you almost slip and fall the other day...?>
Ena: <What?! When did this happen?! Try not to get hurt or anything, okay?! That'd be an awful way to start off the new year.>
Kanade: <Th-Thank you. I'll be careful...>
Mizuki: <Haha. Let's all do our best to have a safe and healthy New Year's!>
